docs.lead_paragraph: The foreign exchange market last week was listless, the modest turnover involving but one major variation in rates, and that in the Swiss free franc which slumped sharply on Friday on selling orders from abroad which piled up on Thursday, while we were on holiday (Thanksgiving Day). At Friday's close of 25.12 cents, the franc showed a decline of 27 points from the preceding week.
